title: Private Military Contractor International - February 2016
description:
English | PDF | 58 pages | 39.1 MB





In this issue we have an interview with a Tactical Legend, Instructor Zero, we go behind trhe scenes with the "grey men" of clandestine commercial surveillance and Craig Reinholds takes a look back at SHOT 2016. ARG Medical introduce us to their new FRECs course and, following Travis Haley's endorsement, we examine the validity of using airsoft as a training tool for real world situations. Trampas takes a Benelli M4 and turns it into a kicking up-specced M1014, we put Pencott under the spotlight and check out the latest from Claw Gear.
